1.9:
Unless the Lord of Armies had left us a small surviving remnant,
we would have been like Sodom;
we would have become just like Gomorrah.

11.9:
They will not hurt or destroy anywhere on my holy mountain,
for the earth will be full of the knowledge of the Lord,
as the waters cover the sea.

16.1:
Send the tribute ram for the ruler of the land,
from Selah toward the wilderness,
to the mountain of the daughter of Zion.

21.15:
They fled from the sword,
from the drawn sword,
from the bent bow,
and from the heat of battle.

24.2:
It will be the same for people and priest,
    for servant and master,
    for servant girl and lady,
    for buyer and seller,
    for lender and borrower,
    for creditor and debtor.

32.12:
Beat your breasts in mourning
    for the pleasant fields,
    for the fruitful vines,

37.35:
For I will defend this city to save it,
for my own sake,
and for the sake of my servant David.

58.13:
If you do not trample the Sabbath
    by doing whatever you please on my holy day,
if you call the Sabbath a delight,
if you treat the holy day of the Lord as something to be honored,
if you honor it by not going your own way,
by not pursuing pleasure or negotiating a deal,
